'''Matthew Russell Wood''' (born [[August 15]], [[1972]]<ref name="SWYT Life Day" />) is currently the Supervising Sound Editor ([[2008]]) employed at [[Skywalker Sound]] in Marin County, California.

==Biography==
Matthew Wood worked on all three films of the [[prequel trilogy]] as supervising sound editor and also did an uncredited acting portion in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']] as [[Bib Fortuna]] and the voice of [[Ody Mandrell]]. In [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] he played [[Seboca]] and [[Magaloof]].

The [[Geonosian]] [[language]] that was known as "[[Geonosian hive-mind]]" was created from three sounds recorded by Matthew Wood under the direction of [[Ben Burtt]] while in [[Wikipedia:Australia|Australia]]. In the city of [[Wikipedia:|Melbourne]], Wood recorded the mating cries of [[Wikipedia:Penguin|penguins]] at a reserve. In the city of [[Wikipedia:Cairns|Cairns]], Wood recorded a group of [[Wikipedia:Megabat|fruit bats]] fighting over a banana. Wood also recorded the sounds of flying foxes. Burtt mixed all of these sounds and created the Geonosian language.<ref name="Blog">{{SW|url=news/drawing-from-the-present-familiar-creatures-in-a-galaxy-far-far-away|text=Drawing from the Present: Familiar Creatures in a Galaxy Far, Far Away|int=Back from the Drawing Board|nolive=1}}</ref><ref name="Much to learn">{{SW|url=news/much-to-learn-you-still-have-8-things-you-might-not-know-about-geonosians|text=Much to Learn You Still Have: 8 Things You Might Not Know About Geonosians}}</ref> Wood first voiced [[B1-series battle droid]]s in ''Attack of the Clones''.<ref name="20 Years Attack of the Clones">{{SWYouTube|cN3xxVrOxbM|Star Wars: Attack of the Clones 20th Anniversary Celebration &#124; Star Wars Celebration Anaheim 2022}}</ref>

As a voice actor, he is best known for his role as [[General]] [[Grievous]] in the film [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']], [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith (video game)|the film's video game]], the [[Star Wars Halloween Audiocast]], the video game ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'' and the [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars|''Star Wars: The Clone Wars'' television series]]. He also plays battle droids, [[Wat Tambor]],<ref name="SWArchive-The Clone Wars Episode Guide: Storm Over Ryloth">{{SWArchive|url=theclonewars/guide/episode019.html|text=''The Clone Wars'' Episode Guide: Storm Over Ryloth}}</ref> [[HELIOS-3D]],<ref name="TCW HC">{{SWArchive|url=theclonewars/guide/episode022.html|text=''The Clone Wars'' Episode Guide: Hostage Crisis}}</ref> [[Senate Guard]]s,<ref name="TCW HC" /> [[BX-series droid commando|Commando droid]],<ref name="TCW HC" /> and [[Poggle the Lesser]]<ref name="comiccon">{{SWArchive|url=fans/news/20090713news.html|text=Get ''Star Wars'' Autographs at Comic-Con}}</ref> in the series.

[[Lucasfilm]] announced on [[October 24]], [[2013]] that Wood would serve as supervising sound editor on the [[2015]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VII The Force Awakens|''Star Wars: The Force Awakens'']]. Wood received an [[Wikipedia:Academy Awards|Oscar]] nomination for his work. Matthew Wood served as the voice of the B1 battle droid [[R0-GR/LEGO|Roger]], one of the protagonists of the [[2016]] [[Disney XD]] television series ''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Freemaker Adventures]]''.<ref name="Premiere Announcement">{{SW|url=news/lego-star-wars-the-freemaker-adventures-premieres-june-20-on-disney-xd|text=''LEGO Star Wars: The Freemaker Adventures'' Premieres June 20 on Disney XD}}</ref> Wood also provided additional voices of death troopers and voice of [[Paodok'Draba'Takat Sap'De'Rekti Nik'Linke'Ti' Ki'Vef'Nik'NeSevef'Li'Kek|Pao]] in ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]''.<ref name="Slashfilm">{{WebCite|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/548704/rogue-one-easter-eggs-sound-interview|text=Auditory 'Rogue One' Easter Eggs Revealed By Sound Editors Matthew Wood And Christopher Scarabosio|author=Sciretta, Peter|date=2017-01-25|work=[[Wikipedia:/Film|''/Film'']]|archivedate=20250129205816}}</ref> Wood, along with [[Ren Klyce]], served as a sound editor for [[Star Wars: Episode VIII The Last Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VIII ''The Last Jedi'']], receiving another Oscar nomination.

